    "summary": "I am working as a PhD Researcher in Climate Change and International Development Studies in Utrecht University. I am investigating the historical adaptation trends of the delta communities of Bangladesh and India; to the climate change hazards.\n\nMy interest lies on Climate Change Adaptation, Vulnerability and Water Security in Global South.  Previously I have worked on assessing the social vulnerability of the high-mountain Himalayan communities to the glacial lake outburst floods (GLOF). I have also experiences of working on Circular Water Economy and wastewater reuse in Urban cities. I have also worked on water quality assessment and identifying pollution hotspot in NCT Delhi, India.  \n",
